            <title><![CDATA[Southern Lebanese skeptical of Israel agreement as violence continues]]></title>
            <link>https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/southern-lebanese-skeptical-of-israel-agreement-as-violence-continues</link>
            <description><![CDATA[When Lebanon's president met President Trump at the White House, it was the first such visit by a Lebanese head of state in nearly two decades. It comes after Lebanon and Israel resumed diplomatic relations under the auspices of the Trump administration, signing a deal meant to end a long history of wars. But as special correspondent Simona Foltyn reports, the deal is facing stiff opposition.]]></description>
